[dubbo-hessian-lite/JavaDeserializer.java at master · apache/dubbo-hessian-lite · GitHub](https://github.com/apache/dubbo-hessian-lite/blob/master/src/main/java/com/alibaba/com/caucho/hessian/io/JavaDeserializer.java#L137):
```java
    /**
     * Creates a map of the classes fields.
     */
    protected static Object getParamArg(Class cl) {
        if (!cl.isPrimitive())
            return null;
        else if (boolean.class.equals(cl))
            return Boolean.FALSE;
        else if (byte.class.equals(cl))
            return new Byte((byte) 0);
        else if (short.class.equals(cl))
            return new Short((short) 0);
        else if (char.class.equals(cl))
            return new Character((char) 0);
        else if (int.class.equals(cl))
            return Integer.valueOf(0);
        else if (long.class.equals(cl))
            return Long.valueOf(0);
        else if (float.class.equals(cl))
            return Float.valueOf(0);
        else if (double.class.equals(cl))
            return Double.valueOf(0);
        else
            throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
    }
```

During Hessian deserialization, the parameter of the non-primitive type in the constructor will be initialized to null. If the parameter is used in the constructor, the relevant exception will be triggered during deserialization.
